title._content: The Hana area of Maui is mostly prime agricultural land and is not immediately threatened by development, November 1973

description._content: Original Caption: The Hana area of Maui is mostly prime agricultural land and is not immediately threatened by development. It is one of the most scenic areas in all the islands and, thanks to the Land Use Commission, will probably remain so for some time to come, November 1973 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-11618 Photographer: O'Rear, Charles, 1941- Subjects: Maui (Hawaii) Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: research.archives.gov/description/554070 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
